**Question:** 

You have a 100 coins laying flat on a table, each with a  head side 
and a tail side. 10 of them are heads up, 90 are tails up. You can't feel, see or in any other way 
find out which side is up. Split the coins into two piles such that there are 
the same number of heads in each pile.

*Solution:*  

Split into two piles, one with 90 coins and the other with 10. Flip over every coin in the pile with 10 coins.

Source: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=M-m9xVF6428
